data.title: Marine Casualty Reports
data.text:
The following is a selection of reports of Coast Guard investigations of marine casualties involving small passenger vessels conducting parasail operations going back to 2010. Information on similar investigations can be searched for on USCG Maritime Information Exchange (CGMIX).

Report: Injury Occurring on the Small Passenger Vessel UPPER CLASS While Conducting Parasail Operations off the Coast of Pensacola, Florida, on July 1, 2016

Report: Material Failure with Passenger Injuries Occurring on the Uninspected Passenger Vessel WHY KNOT Near Panama City Beach, Florida, on July 1, 2013

Report: Loss of Life Involving the Uninspected Passenger Vessel FL0238HY During Parasail Operations in the Vicinity of Hillsboro Inlet Near Pompano Beach, Florida on August 15, 2012

Report: Injury and Loss of Life Onboard the Passenger Vessel X-TREME While Conducting Parasail Operations in Honolulu Harbor Entrance Near Lighted Buoy “H” on January 29, 2012

Report: Injury and Loss of Life Onboard the Passenger Vessel TURTLE While Conducting Parasail Operations in the Vicinity of St. Thomas Harbor, U.S. Virgin Islands on November 15, 2011

Report: Loss of Life Aboard the Uninspected Passenger Vessel ALMOST HEAVEN While Conducting Parasail Operations in Longboard Pass, Florida, on June 27, 2011

Report: Injury Onboard the Passenger Vessel WIND WARRIOR While Conducting Parasail Operations in Mamala Bay, Honolulu, Hawaii on May 21, 2011

Report: Loss of Life Occurring on the Small Passenger Vessel SKY SCREAMER While Conducting Parasail Operations in the Gulf of Mexico Near Clearwater Beach, Florida, on September 05, 2010
